        <headline>Extreme Heat Watch issued June 20 at 2:03AM CDT until June 24 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS St Louis MO</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Dangerously hot conditions with heat index values up to 109
possible.

* WHERE...In Illinois, Jersey IL, Madison IL, Monroe IL, and Saint
Clair IL Counties. In Missouri, Jefferson MO, Saint Charles MO,
Saint Louis City MO, and Saint Louis MO Counties.

* WHEN...From Saturday afternoon through Tuesday evening.

* IMPACTS...Heat related illnesses increase significantly during
extreme heat and high humidity events.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.

Do not leave young children and pets in unattended vehicles. Car
interiors will reach lethal temperatures in a matter of minutes.

Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates.

If you do not have air conditioning in your home or lack shelter,
you can call 211 for assistance locating appropriate shelter from
the heat.</instruction>
